## Remarks  
 <span data-ttu-id="4a549-166"><xref:System.Net.Http.HttpClient> soll einmal instanziiert und über die gesamte Lebensdauer einer Anwendung wiederverwendet werden.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="4a549-166"><xref:System.Net.Http.HttpClient> is intended to be instantiated once and re-used throughout the life of an application.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="4a549-167">Instanziieren eine HttpClient-Klasse für jede Anforderung erschöpft die Anzahl der verfügbaren starker Auslastung Sockets.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="4a549-167">Instantiating an HttpClient class for every request will exhaust the number of sockets available under heavy loads.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="4a549-168">Dies führt zu SocketException-Fehlern.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="4a549-168">This will result in SocketException errors.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="4a549-169">Im folgenden finden ein Beispiel zur Verwendung von "HttpClient" ordnungsgemäß.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="4a549-169">Below is an example using HttpClient correctly.</span></span>  
  
```csharp  
public class GoodController : ApiController  
{  
    // OK  
    private static readonly HttpClient HttpClient;  
  
    static GoodController()  
    {  
        HttpClient = new HttpClient();  
    }  
}  
  
```
